race.comment: THERE GOES MY HERO (1) had little luck fresh, only seeing daylight late before charging home into fifth. Strips fitter and from the inside alley can settle much closer this time. Bold showing anticipated. AUTUMN FROST (3) impressed last start when rolling forward and refusing to yield, with the form around him holding up. Expect him to spear across again from the wide draw and take plenty of catching. TAKING OMAHA (10) couldn't match FLOREY last time when favourite but now meets that rival 5kg better at the weights. Big chance to turn the tables. FLOREY (5) returned with authority at Strathalbyn, finding plenty in the straight after stalking the speed. Toeroek taking over is a strong push. Capable of winning again. FLUTTERING RUBY (4) has made the perfect start to her career and with natural improvement anticipated, she can keep the momentum rolling.
